data.title: A Estrada (English translation)
data.meta_description: Cidade Negra - A Estrada lyrics (Portuguese) + English translation: You don't know how much I walked / To get here / I walked for miles and miles before
data.text:
You don't know how much I walked

To get here

I walked for miles and miles before sleeping

I didn't even rest

I climbed the most beautiful hills

In those dark and cold nights I cried

Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey

You don't know how much I walked

To get here

I walked for miles and miles before sleeping

I didn't even rest

I climbed the most beautiful hills

In those dark and cold nights I cried

Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey

Life teaches and time brings the tone

For a song to be born

With the daily faith I find the solution

I find the solution

When nostalgia attacks, I go to the sea

I close my eyes and feel you coming

You coming

I want to wake up in the morning by your side

And to put up with any problem

I'll rest, in love

On your cozy breast

To see you sleeping and smiling

Is all that I want for me

All that I want for me

I want!

I want to wake up in the morning by your side

And to put up with any problem

I'll rest, in love

On your cozy breast

To see you sleeping and smiling

Is all that I want for me

All that I want for me

You don't know how much I walked

To get here

I walked for miles and miles before sleeping

I didn't even rest

I climbed the most beautiful hills

In those dark and cold nights I cried

Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey

Together, together

Only God can change the way I walk

Only God can change

Only God can change

Together, together
